-LRB- <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Reliance</ENAMEX> floated a <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">$ 357 million</ENAMEX> petrochemical company in <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">1988</ENAMEX> that was , at the time , the largest public issue in <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Indian</ENAMEX> history . -RRB-
The media has raised questions about <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Larsen -AMP- Toubro 's</ENAMEX> issue , pointing out that it exceeds the company 's <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">annual</ENAMEX> sales and its market capitalization .
Even stranger is the case of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Usha Rectifier</ENAMEX> , a semiconductor company with <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">1988</ENAMEX> sales of <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">$ 28 million</ENAMEX> that 's raising <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">$ 270 million</ENAMEX> to build an iron plant .
Once the money is raised , it is n't always certain how it is used .
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Larsen -AMP- Toubro</ENAMEX> , for example , says it 's raising <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">$ 570 million</ENAMEX> to use as supplier credit on large engineering jobs .
